  "release_notes": "Fixes Microsoft Store purchase still hanging in v1.0.25. Microsoft Store's IInitializeWithWindow requires a same-process anchor window with a running message pump; passing the parent Tk window's HWND across the subprocess boundary doesn't work because the Store SDK validates anchor-window process identity. v1.0.26 makes StoreHelper.exe own its own invisible WinForms window and run Application.Run to drive a message pump while the Store call is in flight. Same-process HWND, real pump, overlay renders properly. No other changes vs. v1.0.25.",
